                    "name": "Legal Agreement",
                    "description": "A Legal Agreement means a legally enforceable bespoke and recorded in written form (either paper or electronically) agreement between DB and another party - which may be internal - that involves the exchange of assets or services, and creating obligations enforceable by law.\r\nLegal Agreement can be:\r\n- a distillation of information from one or more documents\r\nand/or\r\n- associated to physical or electronic documents.\r\nLegal Agreement is an abstract type which is implemented, for example, by a specialised agreement e.g. Master Client Agreement, Netting Agreement, Contract of Employment and so on, and may be constructed from a variety of parts, such as Clauses, Terms and so on, and be related to other Legal Agreements, such as Legal Amendments, Annexes and so on.",
