            "name": "Credit Risk Type Management",
            "description": "Credit Risk Control maximises the bank's risk-adjusted rate of return by maintaining credit risk exposure within acceptable parameters. The ability to independently control the Bank’s credit risk profile arising from the lifecycle of a credit transaction (rating, transaction, portfolio management & monitoring and default) providing a comprehensive and independent view of credit risks.",
