                    "description": "Liquidity Risk Data and Reporting Governance and Oversight: Driving and overseeing the implementation of Data Management practices (Data Governance,  Data Architecture and Data Quality & Benefits) to key Risk outcomes including evidencing compliance to the Principles in BCBS239 (RDA&RR).\n\nLiquidity Risk Data Management: Encapsulates all aspects of Liquidity Risk Data Management for the purpose of reporting and metric generation.  Specifically the management of production data mgmt (ref or market data maintenance in-function, physical data sourcing pre-aggregation)risk analytics and manage market data - includes:\n- The manage credit risk data - sourcing and maintaining of key data for the generation of reports and metrics\n- Reconcile reporting data with accounting data\n- Identify required data for reports and analytics \n- Assess data quality, format / errors and carry out data cleaning\n\nLiquidity Risk Metric Generation: Operations & Reporting service encapsulates all aspects of Metric generation - includes:\nIncludes the generation of liquidity risk metrics to assess liquidity risk appetite as defined in the Group Risk Appetite Statement (RAS)\n\nLiquidity Risk Report Management: Define & document reporting requirements for new liquidity risk reporting requests or changes to existing reports (e.g. Liquidity Dashboard) and oversee the implementation. \nMonitor LRM requested reports, provide analysis to the GRC, validate reports and completeness following implementation of model/NME/overlay changes \n\nNormative View Reviews:\n- Review the framework behind the delivery of regulatory metric reporting including interpretation, process, controls and governance following the principles & guidelines set in the Liquidity Risk Oversight Policy\n- Document the outcome of the review",
